section.bhm
	header.bhm-header(aria-level="2")
		h1 Celebrating Black Voices 
		p During Black History Month and beyond, Dr. Martens is celebrating our Black employees and the talented Black creators from our community. They'll speak to us about historical Black figures who have shaped Black culture and the artists, activists and organizations who are pushing the conversation forward.
	
	article#luda
		header.bhm-article-header(aria-level="3")
			h1.bhm-mobile(aria-hidden="true") Luda
			img(src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazon.aws.com/bhm/d3/hero.jpg" alt="")
			.bhm-article-header-content
				h1.bhm-mobile-hidden Luda
				p You may recognize Luda as the effervescent personality repping Docs at our Smith St. location in Brooklyn. What you may not know is he is also a Hip-Hop producer. Influenced by his Haitian roots Luda shares his inspirations and what got him into music.
				.bhm-icon-list
					a.bhm-icon-spotify(href="https://open.spotify.com/artist/76TlFealriTlICvSEcsbE1?si=4VjuJoJ4SXKuiePRXiz9Jw&nd=1" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer aria-label="Visit Luda on Spotify") Luda Spotify
					a.bhm-icon-insta(href="https://www.instagram.com/kromxyscloset/?hl=en" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer aria-label="Visit Luda on Instagram") Luda Instagram


		+vimeoVideo("672157910", "Luda", "https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d3/video-play-button.jpg")


		section.bhm-photo(data-src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d3/module2-king-posse.jpg" aria-description="")
			img.bhm-photo-image
			.bhm-photo-cover
				h2 King Posse
				p One of the most legendary music groups in Haiti during the 1990s. Uniting the country with a mixture of Rap and Reggae. Check out their song #[a(href="https://open.spotify.com/artist/76TlFealriTlICvSEcsbE1?si=4VjuJoJ4SXKuiePRXiz9Jw&nd=1" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Retounen] to get a taste of their energy and sound.

		section.bhm-quote
			.bhm-quote-body My heart was born in Haiti...The music in Haiti is everlasting â€¦ when I was kid I remember dancing to the carnival music.
			.bhm-quote-citation Luda

		section.bhm-photo(data-src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d3/module1-haiti.jpg" aria-description="")
			img.bhm-photo-image
			.bhm-photo-cover
				h2 My heart was born in Haiti

		section.bhm-photo(data-src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d3/module3-kromxy.jpg" aria-description="")
		img.bhm-photo-image
		.bhm-photo-cover
			h2 Kromxy
			p A Black-owned business in Brooklyn that specializes in creating custom apparel and designs. In addition to being a small business themselves, #[a(href="https://www.instagram.com/kromxyscloset/?hl=en" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) the shop] regularly shouts out other local brands and support design programs for kids.




	article#daizsa-jackson
		header.bhm-article-header(aria-level="3")
			h1.bhm-mobile(aria-hidden="true") Daizsa Jackson 
			img(src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d2/1-intro-collage.jpg" alt="")
			.bhm-article-header-content
				h1.bhm-mobile-hidden Daizsa Jackson 
				p Social Media Specialist, Daizsa Jackson manages Dr. Martens social influencer program. Self-proclaimed bookworm and textbook bibliophile, Daizsa is passionate about Black literature. No matter the genre, you can count on her recommendations. Daizsa kindly shared her reading list which features some of her favorite Black writers. 
		
		+vimeoVideo("681098837", "Daizsa Jackson", "https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d2/daizsa-film-overlay.jpg")

		section.bhm-photo(data-src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d2/2-zora.jpg" aria-description="Archival image of Zora Neale Houston wearing a hat and wood bead necklace looking down and off to the side.")
			img.bhm-photo-image
			.bhm-photo-cover
				h2 Zora Neale Hurston
				p Was a #[a(href="https://www.zoranealehurston.com/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) world-renowned author], anthropologist, and filmmaker during the Harlem Renaissance of the 1920s in New York City. She wrote four novels and over fifty short stories, plays, and essays over the course of her life. She is an inspiration for many writers and readers. 
		
		section.bhm-looping-video
			video(loop autoplay muted playsinline)
				source(src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d2/harlem-web.mp4" type="video/mp4")
			.bhm-looping-video-text
				h2 Harlem Renaissance 
				p A #[a(href="https://www.history.com/topics/roaring-twenties/harlem-renaissance" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) cultural revival] of new ideas and Black artistic expression during the 1920s centered in the Harlem neighborhood of New York City. It was an explosion of talent! This era is responsible for some of the greatest American artists of all time; Louis Armstrong, Zora Neale Hurston, and Langston Hughes to name a few.
			
		section.bhm-photo(data-src="https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d2/3-kiese.jpg" aria-description="Archival image of Zora Neale Houston wearing a hat and wood bead necklace looking down and off to the side.")
			img.bhm-photo-image
			.bhm-photo-cover
				h2 Kiese Laymon 
				p #[a(href="https://www.kieselaymon.com/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Kiese] is a Black southern writer whose work has garnered multiple awards and accolades. His book Heavy: An American Memoir was named one of the 50 Best Memoirs of the Past 50 Years by The New York Times. He has several new projects in the works including a reading and writing program for kids and their parents. 
		
		section.bhm-quote
			.bhm-quote-body So much content has been centered around our struggles, but over time Black authors have ventured outside of that box and have told more honest stories. The good and the bad and everything in between.
			.bhm-quote-citation Daizsa Jackson
		
		section.bhm-reading-list(style="background-image:url(https://dm-us-imgs.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bhm/d2/bg-reading-list.jpg);")
			h2 Daizsa's Recommended Reading List:
			h3 Find your next favorite author.
			ul
				li #[strong Homegoing] by #[a(href="https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/authors/2117741/yaa-gyasi/" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Yaa Gyasi]
				li #[strong Heavy: An American Memoir] by #[a(href="https://www.kieselaymon.com/heavy" target="_blank" noopener noreferrer) Kiese Laymon]
